findings.lower_chest: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdomen.hepatobiliary: The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. There is no evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. The gallbladder is within normal limits.
abdomen.pancreas: The pancreas has normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or ductal dilatation.
abdomen.spleen: The spleen shows normal size and attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions.
abdomen.adrenals: The right and left adrenal glands are normal in size and shape.
abdomen.urinary: The kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. No evidence of focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis.
abdomen.gastrointestinal: The appendix is fluid-filled, measuring up to 0.8 cm, with focal hyperemia at the appendiceal base, wall thickening up to 3 mm, and mild mesenteric stranding. No focal fluid collections or free intraperitoneal air.
abdomen.pelvis: Unremarkable urinary bladder and distal ureters. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis.
abdomen.reproductive_organs: Retroflexed uterus within normal limits. Relative prominence of left uterine vasculature, no adnexal lesions.
abdomen.lymph_nodes: No retroperitoneal, mesenteric, pelvic, or inguinal lymphadenopathy.
abdomen.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease.
abdomen.bones: No worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
abdomen.soft_tissues: Abdominal and pelvic wall is within normal limits.
